nc mf worldwide mfw revlon group inc scientific games corporation siga technologies inc transtech pharma website wwwmacandrewsandforbescom macandrews  forbes incorporated is an american diversified holding company wholly owned by billionaire investor ronald perelman current investments include leading participants across a wide range of industries from cosmetics and entertainment to biotechnology and military equipment contents  history  group  holdings  revlon group  gillette four star and the actions of the late eighties  savings and loans  andrews group  meridian sports holdings  morgan stanley  spac  subsidiaries  current  former  see also  references  external links historyedit groupedit macandrews  forbes  co was founded in  by edward macandrews and william forbes a distributor of licorice extract and chocolate in  perelman purchased a  stake in cohenhatfield jewelers and in  perelman through cohenhatfield jewelers bought macandrews  forbes  co through the purchase cohenhatfield jewelers was merged into what became macandrews  forbes group inc holdingsedit in  perelman formed macandrews  forbes holdings inc to take macandrews  forbes group inc private perelman started selling bonds to acquire the remaining  stake in macandrews  forbes group inc also in  macandrews acquired technicolor inc the divisions were sold off and in  its core business was sold to carlton communications for  times the purchase price using the proceeds from the technicolor division sell off macandrews  forbes purchased a  percent stake in compact video inc a television and film syndication company ownership of compact video inc was increased to  in  after the buyout of four star international despite the bond debt in  macandrews  forbes purchased consolidated cigar holdings ltd from gulf  western industries in addition to video corporation of america revlon groupedit macandrews next purchased pantry pride inc in june  its three retail supermarket chains were sold off within months in  perelman also took on his biggest deal yet the revlon corporation financed with over  million in junk bonds from michael milkens firm drexel burnham lambert pantry pride inc offered to buy any or all of revlons  million outstanding shares for  per share when its street price stood at  per share initially rejected perelman repeatedly raised his offer until it reached  per share while fighting revlons management every step of the way forstmann little  company swooped in and offered  per share a brief public bidding war ensued and perelman triumphed with an offer of  per share as a result perelman paid  billion to revlons shareholders but he also paid  million in other costs associated with the purchase after the acquisition perelman had revlon sell four of its divisions two were sold for  billion the vision care division was sold for  million and in  the national health laboratories division became a publicly owned corporation additional makeup lines were purchased for revlon max factor in  and betrix in  they were later sold to procter  gamble in  despite perelmans regular cleansing of upper management and injecting millions of dollars into the company revlon was unable to turn a profit for several years as of the first quarter of  it had had one profitable quarter in the previous  by  revlon was rebounding and its net income had grown to  million as of april  revlon was trading at  per share rising from a low of  per share in  a major cause of revlons financial problems was the debt load stemming from perelmans purchase of the company gillette four star and the actions of the late eightiesedit in  ronald perelman made several attempts on behalf of macandrews  forbes to takeover gillette company offering  billion and eventually  billion in october  perelman withdrew the last offer in  consolidated cigar was sold attempted take overs were targeted at cpc international ronald perelmans controlling buyout of compact video was in  four star international was purchased through a golden parachute deal that was negotiated with david charnay and ron perelman after charnay was notified of stock purchases made by perelman after compact shut down its remaining assets including four star international were folded into macandrews  forbes by the end of  macandrews refinanced the holding companies junk bonds for standard bank loans savings and loansedit main article savings and loan crisis perelman first entered what became known as the savings  loan crisis in  when along with gerald j ford he bought five insolvent thrifts with  billion in assets and  billion in federal aid for  million the five banks originally operated as a single entity named first texas bank but the name changed to first gibraltar after about a week perelmans turnaround manifested as trimming the payroll selling branches and dumping of  billion of underperforming assets in  perelman added san antonio savings association and sooner federal to first gibraltar for  million and  million respectively the purchase of san antonio added  billion of healthy assets  billion unhealthy assets and a  billion government cash advance to perelmans larder while sooner only provided  billion in assets along with the typical government guarantees sooner federal was not only the last sl perelman bought but the first he sold in august  he sold the pieces of sooner to bank of oklahoma and fourth financial corporation for  million the following month he sold the rest of first gibraltar to bankamerica for  million retaining four branches in plano texas and  billion of assets in the mortgage and property management sectors he renamed the four branches first madison its unclear how much money perelman made from his savings  loan deals but its estimated that he made anywhere from  million to  billion with most of the profits manifesting as tax breaks elsewhere in his empire in essence by owning first gibraltar he was able to avoid paying hundreds of millions in federal taxes perelman jumped back into the savings  loan game in a big way in  by buying first nationwide from the ford motor company for  million ford held onto  billion of first nationwides assets valued at  million twothirds of which were considered troubled assets offered to buy back up to  million of first nationwides other  billion of assets that went bad in the future and gave perelman  million to cover potential severance payments perelman quickly boosted its portfolio adding  billion worth of mortgages in exchange for a  million payment to resolution trust corporation before  ended perelman added two more thrifts to his collective sffeds  billion of assets for  million and home federal financials  million of assets and  million of deposits for  million just as quickly as he added assets branches and deposits in california he dumped what he had elsewhere in the country in  alone he sold off  branches with  billion in deposits spread out across five states  went a little slower but not eventfully he acquired california federal bancorp for  billion creating the th largest thrift in the country with  billion in assets in  another  billion in mortgages were added courtesy of wmc mortgage but it was an otherwise quiet year for first nationwide in  perelman negotiated a stock swap with golden state bancorp to create the third largest thrift in the country with  billion of assets the deal left golden states shareholders the majority but perelmans camp still controlled the company everything remained quiet until may  when citigroup announced plans to buy golden state for  billion but ultimately reduced the offer to  billion due to a stock drop citigroups final offer was  shares of citigroup common stock and  cash for every share of golden state exchanged which converted perelmans  million shares of golden state into  in cash plus  shares of citigroup all things considered perelman expected to make about  billion off the deal but because he had quasisold many of his shares in the past he probably gained substantially less than that andrews groupedit andrews group inc is formed from the corporate shell of the former compact video andrews group purchases marvel entertainment group inc in  and later its former parent company new world entertainment inc in  andrews group lost  million with a negative net worth of  million at this time macandrews  forbes owned  in  marvel entertainment group inc goes public with  sold to the public andrews group goes on a buying spree picking up fleer – september  toy biz inc –  stake –  sci television –  stake –  genesis entertainment –  stake – part of new world entertainment in  perelman bought four more stations from the great american communications company for  million and four more from argyle television holdings for  million the purchase of genesis and new world set up one of the spokes for the major  television industry realignment in the wake of foxs acquisition of nfl rights rupert murdoch bought complete control of new world communications for  billion giving perelman a large profit from the sale meridian sports holdingsedit also in  macandrews  forbes acquired the coleman company inc maker of stoves lanterns and camping and other recreational equipment for  million perelman reduced the debt for this purchase by selling the heating and airconditioning divisions by the end of  he had sold everything except colemans camping equipment and boat businesses plus added power tool and recreational vehicle businesses between  and late  he bought seven more companies for coleman in december  perelman and al dunlap met in order to discuss a possible deal between coleman and sunbeam products colemans famous but narrow brand held less growth potential than originally thought and ronald perelman wanted out coincidentally al dunlap was sitting on a financially insolvent company he wanted to dump it took until march  for them to finally come to an agreement with some convincing from his banker morgan stanley perelman sold his entire stake  in coleman to al dunlap in exchange for  billion in cash and  million of sunbeam stock they completed the deal on march  despite a selloff triggering press release from march  that said sunbeam would not meet sales expectations on april  another press release took sunbeams stock from bad to worse it would not only fall short of sales expectations for that quarter but it would barely meet the sales expectations of two years ago the stock went into a tail spin falling from  a share to  a share in a matter of weeks and continued its downward spiral in the following weeks perelman bought control of sunbeam in an effort to salvage the situation but it was for naught the company had to file for bankruptcy within three years morgan stanleyedit on february   perelman filed a lawsuit against morgan stanley two facts were at issue did morgan stanley know about the problems with sunbeam and was ronald perelman misled during the discovery phase the judge became exasperated with what she perceived as deliberate stonewalling on the part of morgan stanley and ordered the jury to assume morgan stanley deliberately and knowingly defrauded perelman hobbled morgan stanley had no choice but to argue that perelman was too savvy an investor to have fallen for their transparent tricks after a fiveweek trial the jury deliberated for two days found in favor of perelman and awarded him  billion the damages stung particularly because morgan stanley passed up perelmans offer to settle the case for  million morgan stanley maintained that the court case was improperly decided citing the judges decision to use florida law over new york law and her decision to order the jury to consider morgan stanley guilty before the trial began in  the courts of appeal reversed the judgement the judges declared perelman hadnt provided any evidence showing hed suffered any actual damage as a result of morgan stanleys actions perelman appealed but found himself shot down by the florida supreme court who dismissed it in a – decision undeterred even after that setback perelman went back to the trial court and asked for the case to be reopened because the hiding of email evidence was a classic example of fraud on the court the trial court rejected his arguments but as of january  he is beseeching floridas th circuit to reopen the case spacedit in  perelman filed the paperwork for a spac special purpose acquisition company called mafs acquisition through his holding company macandrews  forbes holdings a spac is a company founded solely for the purpose of buying out another company but without any preselected target company in perelmans case the company was selling  million units for  each the ipo was being underwritten by citigroup but on december   a year after filing for an ipo mafs opted to withdraw their application for the protection of investors subsidiariesedit currentedit as of  macandrews  forbes held interests in the following companies macandrews amg holding llc am general – amgeneralcom –  share purchased in  deluxe entertainment services group inc faneuil inc mf worldwide mfw harland clarke holdings corp harland clarke corp – harlandclarkecom – formerly clarke american corp checks in the mail – checksinthemailcom harland financial solutions – harlandfinancialsolutionscom valassis communications – valassiscom clipper magazine  clippermagazinecom total loyalty solutions  totalloyaltycom  scantron corporation retailmenot flavors holdings flavors holdings mafco descendant of the original macandrews  forbes licorice business merisant revlon group inc revlon inc scientific games corporation siga technologies inc transtech pharma formeredit alliedbarton andrews group inc formerly compact video inc marvel entertainment group inc fleer skybox toybiz new world communications group new world entertainment sci television genesis entertainment guthyrenker corporation first gibraltar bank golden state bancorp consolidated cigar holdings inc technicolor inc meridian sports holding